        <briefdescription>
<para>This function does a minimal test on the timer counter device and the low level driver as a design example. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>The purpose of this function is to illustrate how to use the <ref refid="struct_x_tmr_ctr" kindref="compound">XTmrCtr</ref> low level driver.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TmrCtrBaseAddress</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the base address of the device. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TmrCtrNumber</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is the timer counter of the device to operate on. Each device may contain multiple timer counters. The timer number is a zero based number with a range of 0 - (XTC_DEVICE_TIMER_COUNT - 1).</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>XST_SUCCESS to indicate success, else XST_FAILURE to indicate a Failure.</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para></para></simplesect>
This function contains a loop which waits for the value of a timer counter to change. If the hardware is not working correctly, this function may not return. </para>        </detaileddescription>
